quran[29]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,154,"What is the matter with you that you make such strange judgements?"
  37,155,"Will you then not take heed?"
  37,156,"Do you have any clear authority for such claims?"
  37,157,"Bring your Book, if you are truthful.{1}",footnotes:1:That is, there can be only two bases for regarding the angels as the daughters of Allah. Either such a thing could be said on the basis of observation, or the one who asserted it should possess a divine book in which Allah Himself might have stated that the angels were His daughters. Now, if those who held such belief could neither make a claim to have observed such a thing nor did they possess any divine book that might contain such a thing, there could be no greater stupidity than this that one should base his religious belief on mere conjecture, and attribute to Allah, Lord of the worlds, such things as were patently ridiculous.
  37,158,"They have established a kinship between Allah and the angels;{1} and the angels know well that these people will be arraigned (as culprits).",footnotes:1:Though the word used is al-jinnah instead of almalaikah, some major commentators have opined that here the word jinn has been used for malaikah in its literal sense (of hidden creation); malaikah (angels) also are, in reality, a hidden creation, and the following theme also demands that al jinnah here be taken in the sense of al-malaikah.
  37,159,"(They say): “Exalted be Allah above what they attribute to Him,"
  37,160,"all of them except the chosen servants of Allah."
  37,161,"So you and your deities"
  37,162,"shall not be able to tempt anyone away from Allah"
  37,163,"except him who shall roast in the Blazing Fire.{1}",footnotes:1:Another translation of this verse can be: Therefore, you and your worship: on this you cannot tempt into mischief anyone except him. According to this second translation, the meaning would be: O you who have gone astray, by this worship that you are performing before us, and regarding us as the children of Allah, Lord of the worlds, you cannot tempt us into mischief. By this you can only beguile a fool who might be working for his own doom. So, we refuse to fall into the trap that you have set for us.
  37,164,"As for us, there is none but has an appointed station.{1}",footnotes:1:That is, not to speak of being Allah’s children, we do not have the power to exceed in any way or degree the place and position and status appointed for each of us by Allah.
  37,165,"Verily we range ourselves in rows (as humble servants)"
  37,166,"and we are of those who glorify Allah.”"
  37,167,"They used to say before:"
  37,168,"“If only we had the Reminder which had been granted to the people of yore"
  37,169,"we would surely have been Allah's chosen servants.”{1}",footnotes:1:This same thing has already been mentioned in( Surah Fatir, Ayat 42).
  37,170,"But when it came to them, they rejected it. They shall soon come to know (the end of such an attitude)."
  37,171,"We have already given Our promise to Our Messengers"
  37,172,"that they shall certainly be succoured,"
  37,173,"and that Our hosts shall triumph.{1}",footnotes:1:Allah’s army: implies the believers who obey Allah’s Messenger and side with him. This also includes those unseen powers by which Allah helps the followers of the truth.
  37,174,"So, (O Prophet), leave them alone for a while,"
  37,175,"and see, and soon they too shall see.{1}",footnotes:1:That is, it will not take long when they will see their defeat and your victory with their own eyes. This proved to be true as it had been foretold. Hardly 14 to 15 years had passed after the revelation of these vases when the pagans of Makkah witnessed the Prophet (peace be upon him) enter their city as a conqueror, and then a few years later the same people saw that Islam had overwhelmed not only Arabia but the mighty empires of Rome and Iran as well.
  37,176,"Do they seek to hasten Our chastisement?"
  37,177,"When that chastisement will descend upon their courtyard, evil shall that Day be for those who had been warned."
  37,178,"Leave them alone for a while,"
  37,179,"and see; and they too shall soon see."
  37,180,"Exalted be your Lord, the Lord of Glory, above what they attribute to Him,"
  37,181,"and peace be upon the Messengers,"
  37,182,"and all praise be to Allah, the Lord of the Universe."
